title: U.S. Government Bonds Weaken Amid Strong Economic Data

organizations.name: u.s. government bonds weaken amid strong economic data

text:
U.S. government bonds weakened Friday as fresh data showed that the domestic economy ended last year on a strong note, fueled by American consumersâ€™ healthy spending.
The yield on the 10-year Treasury note rose to 2.654%, according to Tradeweb, from 2.628% on Thursday. Yields rise as bond prices fall.
